conflict management is an essential
skill required to survive in the highly
competitive environment conflicts at
workplace or home are inevitable
conflict occurs when individuals or
groups do not obtain what they need
although seemingly inevitable conflicts
can be minimized or predicted if the
early indicators are recognized before
attempting to resolve a conflict it is
however important to investigate the
cause of the conflict in most situations
poor communication is cause of the
conflict there are several indicators of
a conflict to begin with an assertive
body language or slight frown on the
forehead can be considered a fair
warning the best to avoid a conflict is
to read the warning signs early and
communicate in cases of resolving the
conflicts the problem should be
addressed head-on communication plays a
vital role in resolution of the conflict
once the problem is identified discuss
difference in values and opinions openly
with everyone honest communication will
help you develop a sound resolution for
effective conflict management avoid win
and lose statements
identify the possible cause disgust and
not argue respect opinions communicate
honestly address the issue and not an
individual presenter logical solution
